<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-R-RELIGION-POLITICS-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GOD AND POLITICS: NOTHING NEW UNDER THE AMERICAN SUN 
</HEADLINE>
  
(Repeating)  (The Week in Review)  
 By WALTER GOODMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   The polite disagreement over the proper place of religion in
politics summons us once again to the works of those ever-useful
observers of American life, Alexis de Tocqueville of France and
James Bryce of Britain. Both of their classic studies,
