</P>
<P>
   $7.99.) Stella Marz, a driven county prosecutor, pursues
</P>
<P>
   criminals infesting a struggling Midwestern city.
</P>
<P>
   11. TARA ROAD, by Maeve Binchy. (Dell, $7.99.) Two women _
</P>
<P>
   one from Ireland, one from England _ learn a lot about
</P>
<P>
   each other and themselves when they exchange houses for
</P>
<P>
   the summer.
</P>
<P>
   12. STEALING SHADOWS, by Kay Hooper. (Bantam, $6.50.)
</P>
<P>
   A psychic convinces herself _ but no one else _ that
</P>
<P>
   a murderer is stalking a North Carolina town.
</P>
<P>
   13. THE EDGE, by Catherine Coulter. (Jove, $7.99.) An
</P>
<P>
   FBI agent searches for his sister, whose disappearance
</P>
<P>
   is intertwined with baffling crimes.
</P>
<P>
   14. THE GUEST LIST, by Fern Michaels. (Zebra, $7.50.)
</P>
<P>
   Two sisters who have been reunited after years apart
</P>
<P>
   give a magnificent party, but an uninvited guest
</P>
<P>
   threatens their new-found happiness.
</P>
<P>
   15. PLAINSONG, by Kent Haruf. (Vintage Contemporaries,
</P>
<P>
   $13.) A half-dozen members of a high-plains Colorado
</P>
<P>
   community learn to contend with the variety of problems
</P>
<P>
   that face them. &QL;
