<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Aunt Rob lived just around
the corner from the Parkers on Herschel Street. She was Granddaddy
Parker's sister, but as I recall, there wasn't a whole lot of
visiting back and forth. I don't ever remember seeing Aunt Rob at
Grandmother's table for Sunday dinner or sitting on the front porch
drinking tea and talking with visitors. I never knew if she'd been
married or had any children. Guess no one thought to mention it.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
