<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0912 -- In the 2000 presidential race, Al Gore and
George Bush have yet to agree on ground rules for the traditional
televised debates, let alone deal with the uncharted risks of
political combat in cyberspace. Nevertheless, the vice president
and the Texas governor have fully integrated the Internet into
their campaigns. (Glass, Cox Washington Bureau) Art includes a
2-column color photo of Gore's Web site, a 2-column photo of Bush's
Web site, an 18-pica color photo of Gore and a 18-pica color photo
of Bush.
