<P>
   RUSSIA-SPY _ MOSCOW _ On Monday, Sept. 11, a Moscow city court
is going to re-examine the case against Edmond Pope, the American
in jail charged with espionage. The court will consider a defense
lawyer's motion to release Pope on bail, or release him from jail
to a hospital, pending trial. Pope's wife, Cheri, and congressman
John Peterson have argued that Pope needs constant medical
attention because he has a rare form of bone cancer that is in
remission. (Coker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22
</P>
