   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _
Reporters can be a pain in the posterior. But describing them as
more particular parts of a posterior is going too far. So when
George W. Bush described a New York Times reporter last week as
``major league'' in a vividly uncomplimentary manner and a
microphone broadcast it to the world, it became a certified issue.
And editors had to decide how to impart this tastefully.. (Lane,
Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED.
