</P>
<P>
   OLY-STOKES (Malden, Mass.) _ It cannot be proven, but many
believe Louise Stokes and her fellow trailblazer on the 1932 and
1936 Olympic relay quartets, Tidye Pickett of Chicago, were victims
of racism and, to a lesser extent, sexism and political factionism.
By Bob Duffy. (2 takes)
