<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENDSERIESBOX0912-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   About the series
</P>
<P>
   Everyone hopes for ``a good death,'' a pain-free death with
dignity, but few take the steps to prepare for such an eventuality,
even though there more more options than ever for the terminally
ill and their families. Cox News Service talked with physicians,
nurses, counselors, ethicists, patients and their families about
end-of-life issues for a series of reports appearing concurrently
with a PBS series, ``On Our Own Terms: Moyers on Dying.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Sunday 9/10 : At age 90, Chuck Gross is determined to meet
death on his own terms.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Monday 9/11 : Are we paying too much for hopeless cases? The
medical, legal and ethical issues.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tuesday 9/12 : The role of doctors in the battle between life
and death.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Wednesday 9/13 : Easing the financial strain on families.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Thursday 9/14 : Losing Carol: One man's love story.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
