<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    'On Our Own Terms' continues
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``On Our Own Terms: Moyers on Dying'' is a PBS series that began
Sunday and continues through Wednesday . The series by Bill and
Judith Davidson Moyers examines the options available for the
terminally ill. The series will be repeated at various times
throughout the week. Each part focuses on different topics.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Sunday: ``Living with Dying'' focuses on the choices faced by
the terminally ill and their families.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Monday: ``A Different Kind of Care'' looks Mount Sinai
Hospital in New York City, where the focus is making death as
comfortable a transition as possible.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tuesday: ``A Death of One's Own'' looks at the steps people
take in the decision of when to suspend debilitating treatments.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Wednesday: ``A Time to Change,'' examines hospice, home and
palliative care.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Web site: The television series' site is at
www.pbs.org/onourownterms.
</P>
