<P>
   BIKE BUILDER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Boyd Atherton of Arlington knew he was
building a better bicycle when he went to work on Tina McMillan's
$900 custom job, but the little rig turned out to be more than just
a set of wheels for her. At 27, McMillan, a Fort Worth stockbroker
with dwarfism, had never ridden a bicycle that she could operate
safely or comfortably. By JOHN AUSTIN. Story has moved in ``a''
general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-CONFESSIONS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Videotape of a criminal's confession is part of the
public domain after the trial, no matter how gruesome, and that
makes possible a new Court TV series called ``Confessions.'' What
it should be called is ``America's Creepiest Videos.'' TV critic
Ken Parish Perkins reviews the disturbing new series that gives
criminals a forum to talk about how they raped, shot or stabbed
someone to death. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-FERMAN-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Summer just won't quit, so pop music critic Dave
Ferman has a suggestion: Listen to music that suggests the cooler
temperatures and contemplation of the fall. Among these: Van
Morrison's ``Astral Weeks,'' The Band's eponymous second CD, John
Mellencamp's ``Scarecrow'' _ and ``Puff the Magic Dragon.'' By DAVE
FERMAN. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-POPSTARS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MESQUITE, Texas _ Another reality show is on tap. The WB network
recently held auditions for ``Popstars,'' its contribution to the
ever-growing pile of reality shows, at a hotel in Mesquite, drawing
about a hundred female hopefuls. Star-Telegram writer Malcolm
Mayhew takes a look at how creepily secretive the WB wants to keep
its ``'Stars.'' By MALCOLM MAYHEW. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Let's talk about tax cuts. No, this isn't a pitch for
George W. Bush's presidential candidacy _ although I will avail
myself of the opportunity to state my belief that the tax reduction
plan proposed by the Texas governor is far superior to the
tax-and-spend shell game favored by his opponent, Al Gore. By BILL
THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
</P>
</TEXT>
