<HEADLINE>
LATIN GRAMMY LINEUP
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROB LOWMAN 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The first annual Latin Grammy awards will be presented in 40 key
categories covering many genres and sub-genres of Latin music.
</P>
<P>
   Emilio Estefan Jr. heads the list of nominees with six
nominations honoring his work with some of Latin music's biggest
acts, including Marc Anthony and Gloria Estefan. Crossover pop
sensation Anthony and Latin songstress Shakira each received five
nominations. Anthony's nominations include Record of the Year, Song
of the Year and Best Pop Male Performance. Shakira's nominated in
Album of the Year and Best Pop Album categories.
</P>
<P>
   Gloria Estefan, Jennifer Lopez, 'N Sync, Son by Four, Christina
Aguilera, Michel Camilo, Celia Cruz, Djavan, Sheila E., Alejandro
Fernandez, Israel ``Cachao'' Lopez, Mane, Ricky Martin, Miami Sound
Machine, Tito Puente Jr., David Sanchez, Arturo Sandoval, Carlos
Santana, Shakira and Dave Valentin will perform at the awards.
</P>
