<HEADLINE>
AIR SO THIN IT'S NONEXISTENT
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below. `Tonight' refers to Tues., Sept. 12, 2000.) 
Our rating: 1 star 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Thin Air'' must describe the room conditions where the folks
responsible conceived of the project. Based on one of Robert
Parker's dozens of novels about tough-guy private eye Spenser, this
one follows the most predictable of plot templates.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Mantegna reprises the role of Spenser, flirting with his
smart tootsie (Marcia Gay Harden), then plugging a thug right
between the eyes. The haggard cop investigating the incident soon
comes to Spenser with a quandary: His hotsie trophy bride (Yancy
Butler) has disappeared; said cop is soon written out of most of
the rest of the script so Spenser can go it alone.
</P>
<P>
   Turns out that attractive dames in Spenser yarns are former
hookers or addicts or, in this case, both; she's being held by a
kinky lunatic ex (Jon Seda, who scarcely exudes the menace every
other character timorously attributes to him). Spenser recruits a
sidekick (Luis Guzman, a fine character actor doing good work in a
role way beneath him) and rescues the damsel in distress.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps most depressing is what this movie says of Joe
Mantegna's career. A decade ago, Mantegna represented the height of
street-sensibility acting credibility.
</P>
<P>
   And now, here he is, squinting in order to create a character
point and otherwise doing a bad Ray Romano imitation. It's
appropriate that Mantegna channeled Dean Martin in HBO's ``Rat
Pack'' movie _ here, he's doing it again, only this time he's
dropping groaner quips that wouldn't pass muster in a Matt Helm
movie.
</P>
<P>
   ---The show: ``Thin Air.'' &QL; 
What: Mystery thriller based on Robert Parker's novel. &QL; 
The stars: Joe Mantegna, Jon Seda, Luis Guzman, Marcia Gay Harden,
Yancy Butler. &QL; 
Where: A&AMP;E. &QL; 
When: 8 tonight. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-11-00 1903EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
