<HEADLINE>
BABY TALK
</HEADLINE>
  Pregnancy prevails at Emmys 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ELIZABETH SMILOR 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Those tuning into E! on Sunday for the Emmy fashion parade at
the Shrine Auditorium might have noticed a conversation theme.
Namely, babies.
</P>
<P>
   Joan Rivers rattled off pregnancy jokes as she and very pregnant
daughter Melissa opened the show. The over-excited Joan referred to
her daughter as her ``chunky monkey'' and after Melissa showed off
for all of E!'s camera angles, Joan quipped that E! also had a
``vagi-cam'' in case Melissa gave birth (she's due this month).
</P>
<P>
   Melissa, also sporting a new dark hair color done just days
before the show, had a little fun herself when ``Frasier's'' Jane
Leeves, who's nearly six months pregnant, stopped to compare
tummies. Leeves also had fun with ``The Practice's'' Kelli
Williams, also expecting, as the two presented an award during the
telecast. Referring to a video montage on TV romance, she said
``all that love, you know where it gets you? Knocked up,'' as she
and Williams touched their stomachs.
</P>
<P>
   Looking great after giving birth only 16 days before Emmy night
was Richard Schiff's (``The West Wing'') wife, Sheila Kelley. He
told Joan that his wife was breastfeeding their baby girl, Ruby
Christine, on the way to the auditorium.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks, Joan and Melissa, we can now say we've heard it all. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
