watchers record shows without videotape and alter the way they
watch live programs. Dubbed ``personal television,'' ReplayTV and
rivals such as TiVo could change the way people use the tube.
Digital video recorders pose challenges for advertisers, however,
because they can make it easier than ever to skip commercials.
Coke's deal could help the company find a way to splash its name in
front of ReplayTV viewers, including through sponsorship of
ReplayTV's high-visibility viewer menu. (Leith, Atlanta
