   OLYMPICS-OZ _ Welcome to the Olympics of Oz. These Games Down
Under, the first of the new millennium, promise to be strange,
magical and wondrous even by Olympic standards. Marion Jones,
Michael Johnson, Maurice Greene, a pack of Austin-based swimmers
and thousands of the best athletes from around the globe are poised
to put on a riveting, heart-swelling and heart-tugging show, the
likes of which are staged only once every four years. The Summer
Olympics command world-wide attention like nothing else in or
outside of sport, and this time around the drama will be played out
against a dazzling and exotic backdrop. Oz is an Aussie nickname
for their homeland. We're not talking an HBO show, but a real penal
colony experiment begun in 1788 when 11 ships of Britain's First
Fleet sailed into the harbor here. This same port can now glisten
as brightly as any Emerald City, especially when fireworks are
cascading over the sail-shaped Sydney Opera House, as they will
when these Olympics begin. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman)
