   OPTIONS-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The Justice Department and the
Securities and Exchange Commission on Monday charged that the four
major options exchanges for years agreed to retrain competition by
not seeking to trade options already traded on other exchanges. The
exchanges _ the Chicago Board Options Exchange, the American Stock
Exchange, the Pacific Stock Exchange and the Philadelphia Stock
Exchange _ signed a consent decree with the Justice Deparment, and
accepted a censure by the SEC, but did not admit doing anything
wrong. By Floyd Norris.
</P>
