   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   OIL-PRICES (Undated) _ The price of crude oil and home heating
oil surged to near 10-year highs Monday, as traders dismissed the
importance of the decision by the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries to increase production by 800,000 barrels a
day. At its current price in the futures market, home heating oil
is now 51 percent higher than the average for last fall and winter
and is sure to become a bigger issue in the presidential election,
especially if October is cold. _ By Jonathan Fuerbringer and Neela
Banerjee.
</P>
