 &HT;    Arthritis booklet
 &HT;    By Amanda Miller
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``?Tengo Artritis? Un folleto bilingue en espanol e ingles''
might have answers you need in Spanish. The new bilingual booklet,
published by the National Institutes of Health and National
Institute of Arthritis and Musculoskeletal and Skin Diseases, has
information in English as well, including symptoms, medicines and
other strategies. It also lists organizations, including the
Arthritis Foundation, 1330 W. Peachtree St., Atlanta, phone:
404-872-7100, or www.arthritis.org.
</P>
<P>
   The NIH also has published a booklet on ``How to Find Medical
Information,'' a step-by-step guide on where to start your search.
</P>
<P>
   For a copy of either booklet, write NIAMS/NIH, 1AMS Circle,
Bethesda, Md. 20892-3675 or call 1-877-226-4267 and ask for the
booklet by name; you also can find the booklets on the Internet at
www.nih.gov/niams/healthinfo
</P>
<P>
   /tengo.htm and www.nih.gov/niams
</P>
<P>
   /healthinfo/howto.htm, or e-mail for a copy to
niamsinfo(at)mail.nih.gov.
</P>
<P>
   _Amanda Miller writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
