<P>
   SITES
</P>
<P>
   Maritime pastime finds an online niche
</P>
<P>
   In the last Around Alone _ the solo round-the-world boat race _
the winning skipper, Italy's Giovanni Soldini, showed his prowess
at the helm and on his laptop computer. Soldini spent hours poring
over his favorite Internet weather Web sites, and his ability to
predict favorable systems and trends proved to be a significant
advantage. The Internet also is altering the way recreational
boaters pursue their pastime. The three largest sites cover races,
offer technical advice and information, boat and product reviews,
and sell equipment or services such as financing or insurance.
</P>
<P>
   www.quokka.com
</P>
<P>
   www.sailnet.com
</P>
<P>
   www.boats.com
</P>
<P>
   Making a pitch to hardcore baseball fans
</P>
<P>
   With more than 7,000 links, this site bills itself as the Web's
most comprehensive collection of baseball-related resources. From
the major leagues to youth leagues, stats and analysis, cards and
collectibles, trivia and history _ as the site says ``If you can't
find what you're looking for, it probably doesn't exist.''
</P>
<P>
   www.baseball-links.com
</P>
