<P>
   (NYT16) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 2000 -- NY-WAX-MUSEUM-2 -- After
six months of construction and seven years of planning, wax figures
were finally arriving in to Madame Tussaud's Times Square house of
wax. The official unveiling of the $50 million showcase is
scheduled for mid-November, although the public will begin to be
admitted in a ``soft opening'' starting in mid-October. A
guillotine to be used in one of the exhibits in the Times Square
site being prepared last week. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 2000 -- NY-WAX-MUSEUM -- Portrait
artist Gillian Griffith works on the wax replica of Yoko Ono as
Whoopi Goldberg's looks on last week. After six months of
construction and seven years of planning, wax figures were finally
arriving in to Madame Tussaud's Times Square house of wax. The
official unveiling of the $50 million showcase is scheduled for
mid-November, although the public will begin to be admitted in a
``soft opening'' starting in mid-October. (Sara Krulwich/The New
York Times) LITE
