documents is ready to replace older encasements that have begun to
break down. On Friday, the National Archives and Records
Administration will let the public see one of the new cases for the
first time. Conservation experts last week place the U.S.
Constitution, in its new casing, into a crate for transportation to
where it will be exhibited at the National Arvhives in Washington.
(Marty Katz/The New York Times)
