Republican strategists once believed was firmly in his column for
November. (Stephen Crowley/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) CLEARWATER, Fla. -- Sept. 11, 2000 -- BUSH-2 -- Gov.
George W. Bush of Texas, right, the Republican candidate for
president, with his brother Gov. Jeb Bush, of Florida, as they talk
with residents of the On Top of the World retirement community in
Clearwater, Monday. Bush promoted his health care and prescription
drug proposals Monday in Florida, a state that Republican
strategists once believed was firmly in his column for November.
(Stephen Crowley/The New York Times)
