<P>
   (NYT26) WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. -- Sept. 11, 2000 --
OLY-MUNICH-EYEWITNESS-COX-2 -- Harry Winkler, 59, a health teacher
at Forest Hill High School in West Palm Beach. Fla., was a member
of the U.S. handball team at the 1972 Munich Olympics, the year of
the massacre of Israeli athletes by Palestinian terrorists. Harry
watched the scene unfold from his balcony, but he actually knew
less than most of us back home because the television news
commentary was in German, which he doesn't speak. Winkler in an
undated photo playing handball. (Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. -- Sept. 11, 2000 --
OLY-MUNICH-EYEWITNESS-COX-1 -- Harry Winkler, 59, a health teacher
