   (NYT20) UNDATED -- Sept. 11, 2000 -- ARMY-JOURNALIST-COX -- Jim
McLaughlin, 55, an Army correspondent, considered himself more
fortunate than the combat soldiers in Vietnam. Much of McLaughlin's
work as an Army journalist consisted of covering ``grip and grin''
awards ceremonies, held in secure areas. McLaughlin wrote many
articles about generals pinning Purple Hearts on wounded GIs. He's
standing near the press vehicle he used in Vietnam. (Cox News
Service Photo)
