   (NYT18) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 2000 -- ALBANIAN-PAGEANT-2 -- At
the first Miss Albania U.S.A. Pageant in New York, 13 contestants,
who ranged in age from 16 to 24 and live mostly in the Bronx, home
to about 30,000 Albanian-Americans, were vying for a $3,000 prize
and a slot in the Miss Albania contest in Tirana. The event was a
patriotic affair for many Albanians, especially with all the
destruction that has occurred in their homeland. Contestants on
stage during the pageant. (James Estrin/The New York Times)
