States each year to spend the winter. Now in the first scientific
study of the region, an international team of researchers report
that this swath of forest has been reduced to peppered remnants in
a sea of farms, homes, cattle grazing areas and logged and degraded
woods. A monarch butterfly in Westchester, north of New York, in
July, 1999, following its migration from its winter haven. (Suzanne
DeChillo/The New York Times)
