<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, SEPT. 12 
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: These corrections appeared in The New York Times on Tuesday,
Sept. 12. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-PA-SWING-STATE-NYT (moved Saturday, September 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday,
September 9 about the importance of Pennsylvania in the
presidential race misstated the name of the Wilkes-Barre newspaper
in which a columnist, Steve -Corbett, wrote about a meeting between
George W. Bush and Bishop James C. Timlin of Scranton. It is The
Times Leader, not The News-Leader.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ALBANIAN-PAGEANT-NYT (moved Monday, September 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, September
11 about the Albania U.S.A. Pageant in New York misidentified the
Albanian national symbol, which was emblazoned on T-shirts worn by
the contestants. It is a two-headed eagle, not a two-headed lion.
</P>
</TEXT>
